(1)
129-147 West Houston Street, south side, from Sullivan to Macdougal Streets, a solid block of six-story tenement houses. Along with the rest of the south side of Houston Street, from Broadway to Sixth Avenue, these buildings are shortly to be demolished.
July 17, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
Window of an Italian bakery at 133-135 West Houston Street, adjoining the S.W. corner of Sullivan Street, a detail of one of the building included in the above view of 129-147 West Houston Street.
July 17, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
